annotation.TEXT: Umm... I kind of wanted to place that shell at the top of the stairs there...
Okay, we're underground.
Hi, Yoshi! You're not a nut, are you?
Well, I'm not going to get boned here, that's for sure!
Oh, yeah. I forgot about this part. Well, maybe I can meet up with Yoshi down there.
Still being generous with power ups, I see.
Dang it, Urchin! Now I can't eat all the fishies! I really hope Yoshi comes back...
Alright! Hi, Yoshi!
Whoa, barely made that jump. It might've been safer to bullet jump, but whatever.
Okay, I figured this block still had a flower, but I just had to be sure.
Ah, yes. This tall ledge. I want to see if I can Yoshi jump up onto it.
These Podoboos still aren't going very high. Is that intended, Greenman?
Heh. That mega mole is pointless. Ooh, the fifth Yoshi coin.
As for what I'll do next, I'll probably pick one of the suggestions I recently received. See ya!
You're Welcome! Pawprint.
However, supposedly there's more to this level now...

Umm... And I don't show this here, but I checked back off camera, and there's no lower route, so you're forced to struggle through these like this if you're big. I suppose this is okay for just a Yoshi coin, but there should be an alternate easier-to-navigate route for the embiggened people.
Ha! Eat it, munchers! ...Wait...
I'm going to eat all the fishies! Ha, ha, ha! And you can't stop me!
I guess this is more atbash. This translates to "Take him and leave". Alright, but where's my nut? I thought I was going to get a nut here!
Wow, I'm clueless. Unless maybe there's a pipe or something off screen below the moon that I can come through later, it looks unreachable.
Yep, the save prompt appeared after I made a move. I guess the castle wasn't a "no-auto-move" level.
Oh, wait. I gotta see that again. How that red koopa just danced his way down that slope!
MOOOONNN!!! But, how do I reach it?
Gulp!
Well, I guess I'm done with this hack, unless Greenman makes another update. So, I hope you all enjoyed watching me play through Greenman's Island of Insanity, version 2!
So, if the two water levels got merged into one, what's going to be where the second water level used to be?
Oh, and while I've got Yoshi, there's something else I want to check out... Let's go to Well on the way. I think that's where the thing I want to check out is...
New Urchin guarding this Yoshi coin.

So, welcome back to more Island of Insanity! Now, Greenman mentioned something about translating stuff into atbash, which reverses the letters' positions in the alphabet (so, A becomes Z, B becomes Y, etc.). And, translating this level's name gives me "GET NUT!", so... we're nut collectors now?
Okay, this is a bit different. Instead of a Yoshi coin, there's a P-switch on a cement block here.
Well, since the owner is here, I guess it's okay if I have him pig out on snacks for a while...
And at least I can count on quickly getting lost power ups back!
Huh? Why move the goal to this separate area? Also, no pipe entrance here?
Okay, quit screwing up that simple action, and make absolutely sure to hold down BEFORE pressing Y!
There's the goal, and I checked back off camera, and there's nothing below the goal besides a huge bottomless pit.
Ooh, that was a cool trick shot.
Ah, this setup's new. So, I needed two P-switches for this Yoshi coin. And, I take it there's more to the level through this pipe?
Heck, yeah. Got another perfect!
I'm guessing the two water levels were merged together here, and of course, the "gimme" Yoshi coins were removed. However, there's no midpoint?
LOL!
Made it! Now, what's in the pipe?
Well, this starting setup's unchanged...
Or, maybe there is a point to the vertical scrolling here?
Alright, next level. Let's see how "Time to swim" has changed...
Nothing? Really? Then, what's the point of this tall ledge and pipe? Come on, Yoshi. Let's get out of here.
No Yoshi because I dumped him in a pit.
Well, looks like I've earned the right to play one last bonus game!
Now, as for that moon...
Ack! Come on, I got this Yoshi coin perfectly the first time!
Okay, Mario. You can stop getting boned now.
Oh, man. Narrow passages through bones.
Okay, it's time for Our last challenge. Now, I think Greenman mentioned something about hating the new version of this castle now. Well, let's see just how bad it is...
Whoops! Bye, Yoshi! I'd better be more careful with my jumps. I don't have any more emergency dinosaurs left.
Forget about the ? block. I'll come back for it later.
Ah, there is. Shouldn't that door have been changed from a boss door to a normal door, then? Anyway, there's a wizard to watch out for here.
Well, this place still appears to be about the same, including the "gimme" Yoshi coins.
And of course, you've gotta have your caged shiny Bony Beetle!
D'oh! I meant to speed this part up, but I forgot to. Oh, well.
No, the vertical scrolling was totally unnecessary for that part. Also, what's with the unreachable duders to the left?
Argh! I got boned! Well, at least the bone thrower walked off into the lava!
Oh, this must be that new superhero that ordinary guys can relate to, Normal Man!
OMNOMNOMNOMNOMNOMNOM!!!
There. Was that so hard? Now, let's back up and give myself some running room, while screen scrolling to keep the shell from despawning...
Okay, Yoshi... You can come back to me any time now... I really hope there's a wall or something for Yoshi to bounce off of up ahead...
Ah, I see this tricky Urchin setup is the same as well.
Oh, yeah. I wonder how you're supposed to dodge this fish if you were big, but not fiery...
MOOOLLLEEE!!!
I'm assuming the P-switch thing is unchanged.
Ah, the castle became crushed properly this time. But, no save prompt? Wait a minute...
Well, this victory march is going to kind of be walled off.
Okay, so now that I have Yoshi, let's see if the message box in Yoshi's House has anything interesting to say while I'm riding him...
Somehow, I expected that pipe to take me straight to Iggy. Why not use a boss door instead?
Wait, where did that crushed castle in the sea go? Did it even exist in the first place? Or am I just going crazy?
Ah, so Yoshi bounced off this pipe, which is new. I wonder where it leads...
Hmm... A running jump plus a boost off of a shell should be enough, I hope...
And, there's a random Goomba here for some reason.
There's another mysteriously caged goal item, this time a squished Rex.
Ooh, new cutscene!
Umm... That Dry Bones just did a disappearing act when the mace appeared. Also, why allow vertical scrolling if there's no point?
Man, not being able to get that moon is going to drive me crazy!
Ah, so this message is different... LOL.
Heck, yeah. Lookin' at a crushed castle in the middle of the ocean.
